FBIS4-12427 "drnes069_a_94002" FBIS-NES-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 ARAB AFRICA Algeria Government Devalues Dinar by 40.17 Percent Government Devalues Dinar by 40.17 Percent LD1004090194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 0800 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004090194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network Arabic BFN [Excerpt] Pending the signing of the one-year stand-by agreement with the IMF, the financial and monetary authorities have announced that the value of the national currency, the dinar, will be devalued as from today by 40.17 percent. Accordingly, $1 will be equivalent to 36 dinars, compared to 25 dinars in the past. The loan and monetary council has also announced a tangible increase in interests on loans. These corrective measures come to confront the current economic stagnation and to ensure boosting the economic mechanism in the future. [passage omitted]
